cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on live migration of VMs in wireless channels, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with virtualized data centers and balancing computing resources, which falls under distributed and cluster computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an optimal bandwidth manager for live migration of VMs, which involves control and optimization of systems. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses energy consumption reduction in virtualized data centers, which can be related to hardware architecture. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with minimizing communication energy under hard constraints, which can be related to information theory.
